@startuml storage_maintenance_window
title Storage Maintenance Window Architecture\nLive storage migration redirects consumers to a secondary device during maintenance

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Helvetica"
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam roundcorner 6
skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor #EAF2F8
  BorderColor #2874A6
  DiamondBackgroundColor #FDEBD0
  DiamondBorderColor #B9770E
}

|Cloud Service Consumer|
start
:Continue accessing storage
(unaware of upcoming maintenance);

|Storage Service Gateway|
:Forward requests to
primary storage;

|Live Storage Migration Program|
:Copy LUNs from primary
storage to secondary storage
(original copy stays active);
:Verify destination LUNs
are fully functional;

|Storage Service Gateway|
:Provide temporary new path;
:Forward requests to
duplicate LUNs on secondary;

|Cloud Resource Administrator|
:Power off primary storage
for maintenance;
:Perform maintenance task;
:Bring primary storage
back online;

|Live Storage Migration Program|
:Restore LUN data from
secondary back to primary;
:Verify primary copy;

|Storage Service Gateway|
:Forward requests back
to primary storage;

|Cloud Service Consumer|
:Access continues
(no awareness of outage);
stop

note right
  Failover system mechanism may
  initiate the migration manually
  or automatically, even though
  maintenance is often prescheduled.

  Resource Replication keeps
  primary and secondary devices
  synchronized.
end note

note left
  Without this architecture,
  a prescheduled maintenance task
  causes an outage in which the
  cloud storage device becomes
  unavailable to cloud service
  consumers.
end note

@enduml
